<1ST_LINE>r i PM-BRF--Italy-Customs     05-11 0115</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--Italy-Customs,0116</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Customs Dispute Resolved Ending Delays At Italian Border Points</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ROME (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Government and union negotiators settled a labor
dispute involving customs officials that had backed up freight at
border points.
   The settlement was reached Tuesday by Finance Minister Emilio
Colombo and union leaders. Colombo said Italy's customs
administration will be reformed to grant customs officers a pay
raise and to redefine their duties.
   Thousands of trucks were backed up at the crossing points with
Switzerland and Austria last week after Italian officers refused to
work overtime to clear customs documents. An official at the
Italian-Swiss border point of Chiasso said the situation was back
to normal after the settlement was announced.
</TEXT>
