<HEAD>American Airlines Jet Makes Emergency Landing In Bermuda</HEAD>
<DATELINE>HAMILTON, Bermuda (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An American Airlines jetliner carrying
90 people on a flight from New York to Puerto Rico made an
emergency landing in Bermuda after the plane's fuel pump
manfunctioned, an airline spokesman said.
   No injuries were reported when the Flight 699 landed on the
British island Tuesday, said an official at the Civil Aviation
office in Hamilton, who spoke with The Associated Press on
condition of anonymity.
   Steve McGregor, an airline spokesman in Houston, said without
elaborating that the pilot decided to land the plane in Bermuda
after reporting a malfunction of the plane's fuel pump.
   McGregor said a DC-10 was sent to Bermuda from New York to
pickup the stranded passengers and fly them to Puerto Rico.
