<DATELINE>MIAMI (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A judge in a paternity suit ruled that a
2{-year-old girl who ``looks like'' comedian Jackie Mason is his
daughter.
   The girl's mother, North Miami actress and playwright Ginger
Reiter, 36, said she met Mason 12 years ago at a Miami Beach
restaurant. She said their relationship was ``off and on'' for a
decade.
   Dade Circuit Judge John Gale noted in his ruling late last month
that the child ``looks like'' Mason and that other evidence and
testimony made it evident that he is the father. A blood test
showed that Mason's probability of being the father was 99.94
percent.
   Matters of child support, medical bills, attorneys' fees and
court costs have yet to be determined by the judge.
   Mason, 57, is the star of a hit one-man Broadway show ``The
World According to Me!''
</TEXT>
