<TEXT>
   Comedian George Burns has some advice for
couples working on their marriages: Don't work too hard.
   The 92-year-old comic speaks from experience; he was married for
38 years to his show business partner, Gracie Allen.
   ``Not only did I love Gracie, I was no place before I met her.
... We had a wonderful marriage,'' Burns said in an interview in
June's McCall's magazine. ``I don't think Gracie and I ever had an
argument in all that time _ except maybe about jokes.''
   ``Don't work that hard at being married,'' Burns said. ``If you
try to make a marriage a success, it's got a good chance to be a
failure.''
