<HEAD>Coast Guard Academy Official Suspended</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW LONDON, Conn. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Coast Guard Academy's assistant
superintendent pleaded innocent to a charge of sixth-degree larceny
after an incident at a department store.
   Capt. W.S. Rich, who was suspended from his post pending the
outcome of the case, entered the plea Tuesday in New London
Superior Court and asked for a jury trial on the misdemeanor charge.
   Rich, 50, was arrested April 26 after a Bradlees security guard
accused him of removing a bag of merchandise from the department
store, Groton police said.
   Rich, who requested the suspension, has said the bag, which
contained several small items, was in a shopping cart between
double doors at the entrance and that it appeared to have been paid
for and abandoned.
   He said he had moved the cart, first inside, then outside the
store, when security guards asked him if he had paid for the bag,
which contained several small items.
