<HEAD>Woman Seizes Mail Carrier, Searches Mailbag</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BILOXI, Miss. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A woman kidnapped a mail carrier at
gunpoint, took him to her home and searched his mailbag, then
released him, authorities said.
   Authorities said they had no explanation for the abduction of
Mason Thompson, 53, on Tuesday.
   Thompson said he was making his appointed rounds when a woman
drove alongside, produced a .22-caliber revolver and forced him to
get into her car, Inspector John Williams said.
   Williams said the woman drove Thompson to her residence and took
him inside, where she searched his mailbag but took nothing before
releasing him unharmed.
   About 30 minutes after the alleged abduction, Mae Lillian Smith,
26, was arrested, charged with kidnapping and jailed under $10,000
bond.
   ``If there was any reason for it,'' Williams said, ``she hasn't
told us.''
