<1ST_LINE>u p PM-GallupPoll     05-11 0187</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Gallup Poll,180</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Gallup Poll Finds Dukakis Well Ahead in California Primary</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Gov. Michael Dukakis of Massachusetts holds a
commanding lead over Jesse Jackson among likely Democratic voters
in California's June 7 presidential primary, a Gallup poll said
today.
   Dukakis was supported by 67 percent of the 487 Democrats
surveyed, to 26 percent for Jackson, with 7 percent undecided or
favoring someone else.
   Dukakis also led slightly in the state in a hypothetical general
election race against George Bush, with 46 percent of 1,205
registered voters backing Dukakis, 42 percent preferring Bush and
12 percent undecided or choosing another person.
   In a hypothetical Bush-Jackson race, Bush led with 58 percent to
31 percent for Jackson and 11 percent in the other or undecided
category.
   The poll also found Republican Sen. Pete Wilson with 51 percent
backing, to 30 percent for possible Democratic challenger Lt. Gov.
Leo McCarthy and 19 percent undecided or favoring someone else.
   The telephone survey was conducted May 5-7; it had a five-point
error margin for the results among Democrats, three points for the
questions asked of all voters.
</TEXT>
