<HEAD>Monkeys Mug Joggers in Revenge</HEAD>
<DATELINE>KUALA LUMPUR, Malaysia (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   About 60 monkeys attacked joggers
and visitors at the Penang Botanical Gardens after a youth stoned a
baby monkey to death, the New Straits Times reported Wednesday.
   ``Several of us saw a large group of monkeys coming towards
us,'' one jogger was quoted as saying. ``Initially, we thought they
were just coming for food and tried to chase them away. We had to
run away when they started charging at us.''
   The animals went after people wearing yellow clothes because the
youth who stoned the young monkey and taunted others on Tuesday
wore a yellow shirt, the daily said. It said no one was reported
injured.
   There are about 350 monkeys at the gardens in Penang, about 180
miles northwest of Kuala Lumpur.
</TEXT>
