<HEAD>Health Officials Fired for Mismanagement</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BAGHDAD, Iraq (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   President Saddam Hussein has fired 22
senior health officials for mismanagement and negligence, the
government daily Al-Jumhuriya reported Wednesday.
   The newspaper said a parliamentary committee has recommended to
Hussein that Health Minister Sadiq Alwash be ``punished'' after
being found ``unfit'' for his job.
   It said the committee had inspected hospital and other health
facilities in many cities over the past two months and found they
were in ``very bad condition'' because of the negligence of their
directors, Al-Jumhuriya reported.
   The newspaper said the fired officials included senior health
executives and hospital directors, but it did not give any details
on the problems that led to the firings.
   The committee was set up in February and authorized to
investigate state-run institutions.
