<HEAD>Gunman Slays Salvadoran Military Judge</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SAN SALVADOR, El Salvador (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An attacker jumped from a jeep
today and shot to death a military judge who handles cases related
to this nation's civil war.
   The jeep pulled up outside Judge Alberto Serrano's home, where
the gunman approached his car and fired four shots, witnesses said.
The attacker then rushed back to the jeep, whose driver was
waiting, and escaped.
   Serrano, 45, died at the scene.
   Most of the witnesses were neighbors, and they spoke on
condition of anonymity for fear of reprisals.
   Past killings have been blamed on leftist guerrilla groups
fighting for power since 1979 and on rightist death squads. But
police said they had no idea who the attacker was.
   Serrano was one of three military judges in charge of national
security cases linked to the civil war, including people suspected
of cooperating with the guerrillas.
