<HEAD>5-Year-Old Credited With Friend's Rescue</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CHILLICOTHE, Ohio (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A 5-year-old boy who was injured after
pushing his friend from the path of a car said Wednesday he feels
like a hero.
   ``He said he had to do what he had to do,'' Sandy Bloomfield
said. ``But I don't want him to be a hero all the time.''
   Her son, Ronald Whitaker, was hurt Sunday when he grabbed
5-year-old Bobby Crink's shirt and pushed him out of the way of a
car.
   ``The car was coming as he was running out in the street,''
Ronald said. ``I had to push him out of the way.''
   Ronald was hit in the leg by the car. He was treated at a
hospital for bumps and bruises.
   ``I was standing on the corner and I saw Ron hesitate and I knew
what he was trying to do,'' Mrs. Bloomfield said.
   Police said the driver hit her car's brakes and turned to try to
avoid the boys.
</TEXT>
