<TEXT>
   Singer Pat Boone says he still considers
Tennessee home, even though he has lived in Beverly Hills for 28
years.
   ``My heart yearns to be back here in Middle Tennessee,'' Boone
said Monday. ``When people ask me where home is, I still tell them
Nashville.''
   Boone was here working on The Nashville Network's program,
``Wish You Were Here,'' a recreational vehicle travelogue series.
   Boone, who turns 54 on June 1, is finishing up work on a new
album. The singer burst onto the pop charts in the mid-1950s with
songs such as ``Ain't That A Shame'' and ``I'll Be Home.''
   Boone performs about 100 concerts a year, and says he would like
to be host of a Saturday night television show to follow ``Hee
Haw.''
