<TEXT>
   A rocket-propelled grenade was fired
at the U.S. embassy in the capital today, but security sources said
it caused no casualties.
   In Washington, the State Department confirmed the attack in
San'a in this republic on the southern Arabian peninsula. It said
the third floor facade was struck and some windows broken.
