<HEAD>Actress Madlyn Rhue to Appear in Ad Campaign for Multiple
Sclerosis</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Actress Madlyn Rhue at first rejected a
request from the National Multiple Sclerosis Society to appear in
an ad for them because she didn't want to be portrayed as a
helpless victim.
   The actress, who is one of 250,000 Americans who suffer from the
disease that attacks the body's muscular system, thought they would
