<HEAD>Nixon: Don't Invite Me to Convention</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Former President Nixon has notified Republican
Party officials that he does not want to be invited to address the
party's national convention in August, a party source said
Wednesday.
   In a letter to Republican Party chairman Frank J. Fahrenkopf
Jr., Nixon said that because he would be writing a column for the
London Sunday Times he would be avoiding any political activity
this year.
   Nixon also notified Fred Malek, Vice President George Bush's
choice for convention manager. Malek worked in the Nixon White
House.
