sentiment among party officials to invite Nixon to address the New
Orleans convention.
   But Nixon, who was driven from office by the Watergate scandal,
was aware that his appearance would be controversial, said the
source. The former president has not appeared at a Republican
National Convention since he left office.
   Bush already has locked up the GOP presidential nomination.
