<TEXT>
   Loss-plagued Lorimar Telepictures Corp. has
agreed to be acquired by Warner Communications Inc. in a $1.18
billion stock-swap deal that adds a top television producer to
Warner's movie-and-music empire.
   Tuesday's announced merger between the two entertainment
companies had been widely expected, because they have been engaged
in talks since March.
   The agreement, which carries a number of conditions, calls for
0.415 Warner common shares to be exchanged for each Lorimar common
