<FILEID>AP-NR-05-11-88 2054EDT</FILEID>
<1ST_LINE>r f BC-Britain-ForeignInvestment     05-11 0202</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>BC-Britain-Foreign Investment,0210</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Foreign Secretary Says Swiss Must Play Fair on Takeovers</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Foreign Secretary Sir Geoffrey Howe said Wednesday
the Swiss government must be prepared to allow British companies to
make takeover bids in Switzerland without legal restrictions if
Swiss companies expect to be able to buy up British concerns.
   ``Swiss companies, for example, expect to make takeovers in our
market. Their government must ensure British firms can make
takeovers in theirs,'' said Howe at an agricultural forum in London.
   The foreign secretary made no direct mention of the 2.1 billion
pound, or $3.97 billion, hostile takeover offer by the Swiss
chocolate company Nestle S.A. for York-based Rowntree PLC, a
British confectioner.
   Jacobs Suchard S.A., another Swiss confectioner, also has built
up a 29.9 percent stake in Rowntree.
   The moves have been highly controversial in Britain because
Swiss companies are protected from takeover by Swiss law.
   Swiss companies are eager to buy operations within the European
Economic Community, of which Switzerland is not a member, to better
take advantage of the lack of barriers to takeovers.
   Howe said the EEC's plan to create a single barrier-free
European market by 1992 would make takeovers more of a two-way
process.
</TEXT>
