<HEAD>List of Hospitals to be Sold by American Medical International</HEAD>
<HEAD>With AM-American Medical.</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BEVERLY HILLS, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   These are the hospitals being sold
by American Medical International Inc. to an employee group in a
transaction valued at $910 million.
   Arkansas: Medical Park Hospital, Hope.
   California: Healdsburg General Hospital, Healdsburg; Mission Bay
Hospital, San Diego; Valley Medical Center, El Cajon; Visalia
Community Hospital, Visalia; Westside Hospital, Los Angeles.
   Florida: Clearwater Community Hospital, Clearwater; Lake City
Medical Center, Lake City.
   Georgia: Barrow Medical Center, Winder.
   Louisiana: Doctors' Hospital of Opelousas; Highland Park
Hospital, Covington; Riverview Medical Center, Gonzales; Westpark
Community Hospital, Hammond.
   Mississippi: Garden Park Community Hospital, Gulfport.
   Missouri: Springfield Community Hospital, Springfield.
   Oklahoma: Claremore Regional Medical Center, Claremore; Doctors'
Medical Center, Tulsa; Southwestern Medical Center, Lawton.
   South Carolina: Doctors' Memorial Hospital, Spartanburg.
   Texas: Alvin Community Hospital, Alvin; Coastal Bend Hospital,
Aransas Pass; Danforth Hospital, Texas City; Denton Regional
Medical Center, Denton; Doctors' Hospital of Laredo, Laredo; Fort
Bend Community Hospital, Missouri City; Katy Medical Center, Katy;
Medical Arts Hospital, Dallas; Medical Arts Hospital, Texarkana;
Medical Plaza Hospital, Sherman; North Texas Medical Center,
McKinney; Odessa Women's & Children's Hospital, Odessa; Parkway
Hospital, Houston; Physicians' & Surgeons' Hospital, Alice;
Riverside Community Hospital, Corpus Christi; Round Rock Community
Hospital, Round Rock; Terrell Community Hospital, Terrell; Westbury
Hospital, Houston.
